did.unittitle: Edwin and Terry Murray collection of newsprint comic strips
did.abstract: Collection consists of Edwin and Terry Murray's collection of clipped comic strips from newspapers, including Blondie, B.C., Gasoline Alley, Gordo, Buz Sawyer, Apartment 3-G, Bugs Bunny, Archie, Mary Worth, Moon Mullins, Out Our Way, Judge Parker, Steve Canyon, Kerry Drake, Campus Clatter, Chief Wahoo, Priscilla's Pop, Green Beret, Hi and Lois, Boner's Ark, Dennis the Menace, The Jackson Twins, RIP Kirby, Wizard of Id, Smilin' Jack, Beetle Bailey, Popeye, and many others; as well as assorted full comics sections (also known as funnies) from American newspapers such as The Washington Post, the New Orleans Times-Picayune, the Overseas Weekly, the Detroit Free Press, The Chicago Defender, Asbury Park Sunday Press, The Durham Sun, The Durham Morning Herald, The Greenville News, and The News and Observer (Raleigh, N.C.). The bulk of the comic strips date from the 1950s through 1970s.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Collection is sorted into series: Clipped Strips and Newspaper Comics Sections.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Edwin L. and Terry A. Murray, brothers residing in Durham, North Carolina, have been collectors of comic books and other pulp culture for fifty years.

userestrict.head: Use Restrictions
userestrict.p: The copyright interests in this collection have not been transferred to Duke University. For more information, consult the copyright section of the Regulations and Procedures of the David M. Rubenstein Rare Book & Manuscript Library.

acqinfo.head: Provenance
acqinfo.p: The Edwin and Terry Murray Collection of Newsprint Comic Strips were received by the David M. Rubenstein Rare Book & Manuscript Library as a gift in 2019.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: [Comic Title, Artist, Date, Newspaper title (if known)], Edwin and Terry Murray Collection of Newsprint Comic Strips, David M. Rubenstein Rare Book & Manuscript Library, Duke University.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Processed by Meghan Lyon, Bethany Lynch, June 2019; Laurin Penland, Bethany Lynch, November 2019 and February 2020.
Accessions described in this collection guide: 2019-0077, 2019-0124, and 2019-0142.

relatedmaterial.head: Related Materials
relatedmaterial.p: The Rubenstein Library also holds the Edwin and Terry Murray Collection of Fanzines; the Edwin and Terry Murray Collection of Pulp Culture; and the Edwin and Terry Murray Collection of Role-playing Games. Search "Edwin and Terry Murray" as an author in the catalog to find additional comic books, cataloged separately.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Series consists of clipped newspaper and newsprint comic strips collected by the Murrays and bundled by title and date. Items have been filed as best as possible in loose chronological order, arranged alphabetically by title of the comic strip.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Series contains newspaper comic sections for assorted newspapers, collected by the Murrays documenting the range of comic strip titles published within each newspaper. Runs are incomplete and scattered, and the physical condition of each newspaper issue varies.
